    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing mutex protection in F1AP cell info comparison\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP library was missing proper mutex protection when accessing shared cell information structures. This could lead to race conditions and data corruption in multi-threaded environments.\n\nThis fix implements the missing `eq_f1ap_cell_info` function and adds proper mutex protection around critical sections.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_common.c`: Added new file with implementation of `eq_f1ap_cell_info` function\n- `openair2/COMMON/f1ap_messages_types.h`: Added function declaration\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.h`: Exported mutex for external access\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_rrc_message_transfer.c`: Added mutex protection around shared state access\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_ue_context_management.c`: Added mutex protection around shared state access\n- `CMakeLists.txt`: Added new source file to build\n\n### Reproduction\nIn a multi-threaded F1AP environment with concurrent DU connections, accessing `getCxt(0)->setupReq.cell[0].info` without proper synchronization could result in:\n- Inconsistent cell information reads\n- Data corruption in cell configuration\n- Potential segfaults when accessing freed or partially updated structures\n\nThe issue is most likely to manifest under high load conditions with frequent F1 setup requests.\n"
}